# AI Provider Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and add your API keys

# OpenAI Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Uncomment and add your key to enable OpenAI GPT-4 Vision integration
# EXPO_PUBLIC_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-api-key-here

# Note: In Expo, environment variables must be prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_
# to be accessible in your React Native code

# Alternative AI Providers (for future implementation)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-key
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-google-key

# Usage Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Add your OpenAI API key to the .env file
# 3. Install OpenAI SDK: npm install openai
# 4. Uncomment the OpenAI implementation in services/ai.ts
# 5. The chatbot will automatically use OpenAI when an API key is detected

# Security Note:
# - Never commit your .env file to version control
# - The .env file should be listed in .gitignore
# - For production apps, use secure environment variable management
